The article emphasizes the need for every person in America to be free from gun violence. It mentions recent incidents, such as a shooting at the University of Nevada, Las Vegas, and a string of violence in Texas. The authors express their condolences for the victims and their families and highlight the daily toll of gun violence in the country. They call for Congress to implement universal background checks, pass red flag laws, and renew the assault weapons ban. The article also mentions President Biden's commitment to advancing gun safety policies through the White House Office of Gun Violence Prevention.